A good comparison would be having a wizard pre manaburn nerf, finding a 16K hp mob that quads for 1200 lets say and summons, and use manaburn on the mob, gambling that on that one shot you crit for 16k+. You don't crit, it's instant death. You don't crit high enough, it's instant death. Now take this high risk, and prolong it from instant to the 5-6 min it takes to kill Wuoshi and to not have anything at all go wrong, and you will see that the odds are heavily against you. Which is why I don't forsee every enchanter around killing dragons since while it's possible to do it on the first try, it's also possible to die 50 times and never kill Wuoshi.<br>
<br>
Wuoshi is also only doable, because in Wakening Lands there is an overpowered underconned mob which gravity fluxes for 1200 known as Rolendal. Take away the ability to charm Rolendal (by either making him uncharmable or raising his level to 65) and Wuoshi is no longer soloable. It's also why you don't see people go after Gore or Severilous, there isn't anything in the zone that can stand up to them. Charm is only as powerful as the mobs are.<br>
<br>
Turonyen<br>
Level 65 Enchanter<br>
